## Legal & Compliance (California)

### Entity structure
- Must form a **Professional Corporation (PC)** in CA — NOT a standard LLC
- Clinical services cannot operate under a regular LLC in California
- Coco owns the PC; Kelly handles business ops entity separately if needed

### Clinical authority
- Coco is NOT independent NP — needs **Standardized Procedure Agreement (SPA)**
- SPA must specifically cover: IV therapy, mobile services, emergency protocols, prescribing fluids/additives
- Shortcut: Use medical director infrastructure partner

### Medical director options (evaluate both)
- **Prax Health** (praxhealth.com) — medical infrastructure layer for independent providers
- **Guardian Medical Direction** — alternative to compare
- Either provides: MD supervision, protocol templates, prescribing framework, compliance structure

### Malpractice
- Minimum: $1M per claim / $3M aggregate
- Must explicitly cover: mobile IV, off-site care, emergency meds
- Carriers: NSO, CM&F, Proliability
- Get written confirmation that "elective IV hydration" is covered
- Do NOT take a single client before policy is active

### Other compliance items
- Furnishing number must be active
- DEA registration (for Zofran, Toradol, prescription additives)
- HIPAA-compliant EHR (IntakeQ or SimplePractice for Phase 1)
- Written IV protocols + informed consent forms
- Emergency kit: Epi, Benadryl, BP cuff, oxygen access plan
- Sharps disposal + medical waste contract
- City business license (Oakland)

### Nevada (Incline Village) — defer
- CA license does NOT cover Nevada practice
- Requires separate Nevada APRN license (8–12 week processing)
- Do NOT begin until CA generating $10K+/month for 2+ months

